 make it happen.\u201d\n\nWhatmore is a Sri Lanka born Australian cricket coach and former cricketer. He was the Head coach of Sri Lanka when Sri Lanka won the Cricket World Cup in 1996. He is an old boy of the prestigious Royal College Colombo.\n\nA right-handed batsman, Whatmore played seven Test matches for Australia in 1979, and one One Day International in 1980. At first-class level, he scored over 6,000 runs for Victoria.","title":"Dav Whatmore likely to be Nepali cricket Head Coach - Khabarhub","url":"http://english.khabarhub.com/2020/12/148311/","video":[]}
